The taxonomic position of the genus Parablattogryllus Storozhenko, 1988 (Insecta) from the Cretaceous of Russia
Article
Full-text available
  • Jan 2011
  • D. S. Aristov
  • Sergey Yu Storozhenko
The holotype of Parablattogryllus obscurus Storozhenko, 1988 from the Lower Cretaceous locality Baissa in East Siberia is re-described and illustrated. The genus Parablattogryllus Storozhenko, 1988 is transferred from the family Blattogryllidae of the order Grylloblattida to the infraclass Polyneoptera as the genus of uncertain systematic position.

Permian fossil insects of North-East Europa: Revision of the family Atactophlebiidae (Ins. Gerarida, Atactophlebiidae)
Article
  • Apr 2008
  • Sergey Yu Storozhenko
Revision of family Atactophlebiidae is made. Olgaephilus emendatus gen. et sp. n. from Upper Permian of Arkhangelsk region is described. On the basis of wing-venation and structure of body family Atactophlebiidae must be transferred from order Grylloblattida (= Paraplecoptera) to the order Gerarida.
